and slowing down input;
#X text -67 155 oneARDANALinBUTTONout for when we have button attached
to analog input of arduino it outputs 0 to \$1 +/- offset value \,
can make a counter with one button \, also can output 1 bang on each
press;
#X text -67 273 oneARDANALinASdigitalSWITCH when we have a SWITCH attached
to analog input this will output 0 or 1 \, can be reversed 1 / 0 when
argument \$1 changed;
#X text -66 316 argument for oneARDANALinASdigitalSWITCH \$1 - 0 lub
1 to flip the output values;
#X text -67 408 oneARDANALpinROTARYswitch when we have a rotary SWITCH
attached to analog input;
#X text -66 437 no arguments \, outputs from 1 to 6;
